; DOMAIN: topology [CLOSED, derived 2026-07-24] ; Claim: an arbitrary product of compact spaces is compact (Tychonoff). ; Structure: (family {X_i} each-compact) (product-topology P). ; Result: P compact; proof via ultrafilter convergence / Alexander subbase. ; Minimal: componentwise-compactness + product-topology => global compactness (uses choice). ; Bridge: infinite-product stability — mirrors product-of-measures (measure_extension) and product decomposition (crt/category). (= (compact (product $family)) (all-compact $family))